# The governance gate cannot protect itself: for `pull_request`, GitHub runs the
# workflow definition from the pull request, so a change can rewrite the gate that
# judges it. Code owner review is the anchor that lives outside the pull request.
#
# This file only has effect once "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in
# branch protection for the protected branches. Without that setting it is inert.
#
# Replace @OWNER with the real owning user or team.

# The gate's own workflow definition — the one thing a pull request could otherwise
# rewrite to score itself green.
/.github/workflows/    @OWNER
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @OWNER

# Gate entrypoint, scoring code, and the rules it enforces.
/bin/change-assess                @OWNER
/lib/adaptive_change_governance/  @OWNER
/plugins/                         @OWNER
/.ai-governance/                  @OWNER
